From 341b3a7581a65404748bffecce02e3d87a3469d0 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Tyson Trautmann <tysont@gmail.com>
Date: Fri, 27 Mar 2026 13:02:13 -0700
Subject: [PATCH] Add remote database support via libsql Builder::new_remote
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Add pure network-only database connections where all queries are sent
to a remote server over WebSocket/HTTP with no local file. This
enables the AgentFS FUSE daemon to operate against a database hosted
remotely (e.g., in a Cloudflare Durable Object).

SDK changes:
- ConnectionPool::new_remote(url, auth_token) — creates a pool backed
  by libsql::Builder::new_remote(), connecting via Hrana protocol
- AgentFSOptions::with_remote(url) + .with_auth_token(token) — new
  constructor for remote mode, skips local path resolution
- AgentFS::open() — detects remote_url in options and creates the
  pool via new_remote() instead of new_local()

CLI changes:
- agentfs mount --remote-url <URL> [--auth-token <TOKEN>] <name> <dir>
  Mounts a remote database via FUSE or NFS. Schema version check is
  skipped for remote connections (schema managed by remote server).
- MountArgs carries remote_url and auth_token through to both
  mount_fuse() and mount_nfs_backend()

All existing local-file functionality unchanged. 100 tests pass.

Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.6 (1M context) <noreply@anthropic.com>
